description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF continued to work with partners and stakeholders based in eastern Ukraine as a reliable and trusted partner to advance the agenda on the rights of children. Working from four locations, UNICEF staff engaged with the government partners, particularly with the municipal authorities to support them in improving the existing services for vulnerable children and also establish new services for children with disabilities. UNICEF advocated for increased humanitarian access to enable better assessment of the needs and also provide targeted humanitarian assistance. As a result, all programme targets for the year have been achieved. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:25/01/2022
